transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I got a prescription order sent to me yesterday and I never had, I never gave anybody authorization to run my credit card again and send me another prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, our service, it does come with prescription refills.

Speaker 2: What's that?

Speaker 1: I said our service, the prescription does come with refills, so that's probably why you received another one, but I can help you with your account.

Speaker 2: What's your name and your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Barry Devereaux, 226-67.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I don't want anybody charging my credit cards anymore without my authorization.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I see that you have a prescription for the Viagra 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: As I mentioned that the service does come with refills, but you're not obligated to get them as often every month.

Speaker 2: If it is something that you do plan on taking down the line to keep your prescription active, we can adjust your frequency to every six months.

Speaker 1: Just pause it for right now, I don't need anymore right now.

Speaker 2: Okay, pause it without a refill date, it's cancelling the prescription, and so if you do decide to order down the line, you'll have to like start all over again and the second time.

Speaker 1: Well then just do it at six months.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Just do it at six months.

Speaker 2: Okay, and then you can always reorder before then or delay it if you need to.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I won't see any more for six months.

Speaker 2: Right, that is correct.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: You too.
